14800.name: Afro Perm Wig - Pink
14800.description: Lush Afro perm hair. Cannot undo equip

14801.name: Gludio Guard Earring
14801.description: Ring given to the royal guard of Gludio territory. Stun Attack +15%, Bleed Defence +15%, Water Power Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Gludio

14802.name: Dion Guard Earring
14802.description: Ring given to the royal guard of Dion territory. Hold Attack +15%, Resistance to Poison +15%, Resistance to Holy +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Dion

14803.name: Giran Guard Earring
14803.description: Ring given to the royal guard of Giran territory. Bleed Attack +15%, Paralysis Defence +15%, Wind Power Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Giran

14804.name: Oren Guard Earring
14804.description: Necklace given to the royal guard of Oren territory. Paralysis attack +15%, hold Defence +15%, darkness Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Oren

14805.name: Aden Guard Earring
14805.description: Earring given to the royal guard of Aden territory. Mind Attack +15%, Stun Defence +15%, Earth Power Defence +10. CP +5% increase. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing two earrings with the same effect. Royal Guard Earring - Aden

14806.name: Innadril Guard Earring
14806.description: Earring given to the royal guard of Innadril territory. Sleep Attack +15%, Stun Defence +15%, Water Power Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Innadril

14807.name: Goddard Guard Earring
14807.description: Earring given to the royal guard of Goddard territory. Stun Attack +15%, Sleep Defence +15%, Fire Power Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Goddard

14808.name: Rune Guard Earring
14808.description: Earring given to the royal guard of Rune territory. Poison Attack +15%, Hold Defence +15%, Fire Power Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Rune

14809.name: Schuttgart Guard Earring
14809.description: Necklace given to the royal guard of Schuttgart territory. Hold Attack +15%, Fear Defence +15%, Wind Power Defence +10. CP +5%. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Only one effect is applied when wearing the same two earrings. Royal Guard Earring - Schuttgart

14810.name: Blue Talisman - Buff Cancel
14810.description: Cancels the buffs of nearby enemies upon use. Only one effect is applied when you wear the same two talismans. Shadow Item with no exchange/drop available Blue Talisman of Buff Cancel

14811.name: Blue Talisman - Buff Steal
14811.description: Steals the target's abnormal status upon use. Only one effect is applied when you wear the same two talismans. Shadow Item with no exchange/drop available Blue Talisman of Buff Steal

14812.name: Red Talisman - Territory Guard
14812.description: When used, Max CP is greatly increased and a certain amount of CP is greatly recovered. Only one effect is applied when you wear the same two talismans. Shadow Item with no exchange/drop available Red Talisman of Territory Guard

14813.name: Blue Talisman - Lord's Divine Protection
14813.description: Upon use, greatly decreases the damage received during PvP. Only one effect is applied when you wear the same two talismans. Shadow Item with no exchange/drop available Blue Talisman of Lord's Divine Protection

14814.name: White Talisman - All Resistance
14814.description: Increases Resistance to all elements. Effect does not stack with additional Talismans of the same type. This item cannot be traded or dropped. White Talisman of Attribute Resistance

14815.name: Territory Health Recovery Potion
14815.description: Recovers HP when in use. Restricted to characters higher than level 61 and lower than level 75. Can only be used on the battlefield during a Territory War. Battlefield Use Secret Medicine of Life

14816.name: Territory Mana Recovery Potion
14816.description: Recovers MP when in use. Restricted to characters higher than level 61 and lower than level 75. Can only be used on the battlefield during a Territory War. Battlefield Use Secret Medicine of Mind

14817.name: Territory CP Recovery Potion
14817.description: Recovers CP when in use. Restricted to characters higher than level 61 and lower than level 75. Can only be used on the battlefield during a Territory War. Battlefield Use Secret Medicine of Will

14818.name: Enriched Pet Food for Wolves
14818.description: Pet food for Great Wolves and Fenrirs. When your pet's hunger gauge drops below 55% they will be able to feed themselves automatically. H5 Price Feed for Enriched Enhanced Pets

14819.name: Guardian's Dragon Bugle
14819.description: A bugle used to summon a Guardian's Strider. This pet uses some of the experience points earned by its master. Wolf's Necklace

14820.name: Skull Key of Suffering
14820.description: Key used to remove the time restriction on instance and allows you to enter the Hall of Suffering. Can only be used once a day outside the entrance to the Hall of Suffering. Cannot use multiple skull keys daily. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Can be stored in a private warehouse. Skull Key of Pain

14821.name: Skull Key of Erosion
14821.description: Key used to remove the time restriction on instance and allows you to enter the Hall of Erosion. Can only be used once a day outside the entrance to the Hall of Erosion. Cannot use multiple skull keys daily. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Can be stored in a private warehouse. Skull Key of Erosion

14822.name: Skull Key of the Heart
14822.description: Key used to lift the entrance limit to the Hall of Suffering. Can only be used once a day outside the instance. After use, the effect disappears when the instance is reset. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Can be stored in a private warehouse. Skull Key of the Heart

14823.name: Soul Extraction Device
14823.description: Device that can be used on a recently killed monster in the Seed of Infinity to collect additional Tears of a Freed Soul. Can be used only inside Seed of Infinity instant dungeons. Cannot be exchanged or dropped. Can be stored in a private warehouse. Soul Extraction

14828.name: Deinonychus Mesozoic Stone
14828.description: Stone used to summon a Deinonychus. This pet can consume Food For Wolves to replenish hunger. It takes away some of the experience points the Pet Master earns. Wolf's Necklace

14829.name: Cave Exploration Text 1 Sheet
14829.description: Report of explorers that contains information about the cave's origins

14830.name: Cave Exploration Text 2 Sheet
14830.description: Report of explorers that contains information about the cause of transformation of the ancient giants

14831.name: Cave Exploration Text 3 Sheet
14831.description: Report of explorers that contains information about the secret of Hekaton Prime

14832.name: Growth Accelerator
14832.description: Syringe containing Stakato secretion. When injected into a Bizarre Cocoon, this substance will stimulate the growth of a Cannibalistic Stakato Chief. Growth Accelerator

14833.name: Small Stakato Cocoon
14833.description: Tightly wrapped item that resembles a cocoon. But it doesn't seem to contain a lifeform. Small size. Small Staccato Silk Cocoon

14834.name: Large Stakato Cocoon
14834.description: Tightly wrapped item that resembles a cocoon. But it doesn't seem to contain a lifeform. Fairly heavy. Big Staccato Silk Cocoon

14835.name: Multi-colored Jewel
14835.description: Lump of ore containing mysterious power. Upon use, you are teleported to the Stakato nest entrance. Clear Five-Colored Crystal

14836.name: Knowledge of the Giants Anthology, Chapter 1
14836.description: Portion of the knowledge anthology from the Titans era. Chapter 1 of 5.

14837.name: Knowledge of the Giants Anthology, Chapter 2
14837.description: Portion of the knowledge anthology from the Titans era. Chapter 2 of 5.

14838.name: Knowledge of the Giants Anthology, Chapter 3
14838.description: Portion of the knowledge anthology from the Titans era. Chapter 3 of 5.

14839.description: Portion of the knowledge anthology from the Titans era. Chapter 4 of 5.

14840.name: Knowledge of the Giants Anthology, Chapter 5
14840.description: Portion of the knowledge anthology from the Titans era. Chapter 5 of 5.

14841.name: Ancient Parchment
14841.description: Parchment from the Titans era. Double click to see more information. Ancient Parchment

14842.name: Wisdom of the Giants Text, Chapter 1
14842.description: Book containing a collection of wisdom from the Titans era. Chapter 1 of 5.

14843.name: Wisdom of the Giants Text, Chapter 2
14843.description: Book containing a collection of wisdom from the Titans era. Chapter 2 of 5.

14844.name: Wisdom of the Giants Text, Chapter 3
14844.description: Book containing a collection of wisdom from the Titans era. Chapter 3 of 5.

14845.name: Wisdom of the Giants Text, Chapter 4
14845.description: Book containing a collection of wisdom from the Titans era. Chapter 4 of 5.

14846.name: Wisdom of the Giants Text, Chapter 5
14846.description: Book containing a collection of wisdom from the Titans era. Chapter 5 of 5.

14847.name: Titan Ancient Book
14847.description: Book from the Titans era. Double click to see more information. Titan's Ancient Book

14848.name: Protection Soul's Pendant
14848.description: Amulet with protection from the evil spirits of the altar. Soul cores are purged above and driven into the pendant to make it shine with a red glow.

14849.name: Kahman's Supply Box
14849.description: Supply box received from Mercenary Kahman as mission compensation. Double click to check more information.

14850.name: Droph's Support Items
14850.description: Support items received from Dwarven Explorer Droph for defeating Hekaton Prime. Double click to check more information.

14851.name: Cave Exploration Text 1 Sheet
14851.description: Report of explorers that contains information about the cave's origins

14852.name: Cave Exploration Text 2 Sheet
14852.description: Report of explorers that contains information about the cause of transformation of the ancient giants

14853.name: Cave Exploration Text 3 Sheet
14853.description: Report of explorers that contains information about the secret of Hekaton Prime

14854.name: Recipe - Spiteful Soul Energy
14854.description: Recipe for quests. Needed to make soul energy. Requires the Create Item skill level 2.

14855.name: Spiteful Soul Energy
14855.description: Energy form soul received from the spiteful soul Leader. Collect and bring them to Balthazar.

14856.name: Spiteful Soul Vengeance
14856.description: Vindictive spirit received from the spiteful soul Leader. Cannot be formed into energy and is pretty much useless.

14857.name: Shell of Monsters
14857.description: Hard shell obtained by defeating the monsters near the cave of the giants. Take it to Magister Hanellin.

14858.name: Scout's Note
14858.description: Note obtained from the scout's body. Deliver the note to Mercenary Captain Pierce.

14859.name: Stakato Queen's Fang
14859.description: Fang obtained from defeating Stakato Queen Shyeed. Bring it to Mercenary Kahman.

14860.name: Box Containing the Flame of the Holy Spirit
14860.description: Box protecting the flame of the Holy Spirit. Deliver it to Beacon Town Manager Torrant at the Den of Evil.

14861.name: Cursed Burial Items
14861.description: Item that gives physical power to souls with deep grudges.

14862.name: Flauen's Letter
14862.description: Letter from Gatekeeper Flauen of Heine. If you bring it to Iason Heine, you can hear more information about the mission.

14863.name: Letter to Helvetica
14863.description: Certificate containing Iason Heine's promise of support. Bring it to Dr. Helvetica at the Field of Silence Research Center located in the Field of Silence.

14864.name: Letter to Athenia
14864.description: Certificate containing Iason Heine's promise of support. Bring it to the Priestess Athenia of the Ritual Site of Purge located in the Field of Silence.

14865.name: Certificate of Support
14865.description: Certificate received from Dr. Helvetica of the Field of Silence Research Center. This certificate is necessary to receive an additional mission from him.

14866.name: Certificate of Support
14866.description: This certificate shows your support for Priestess Athenia and her cause. This certificate is necessary to receive an additional mission from her.

14867.name: Damaged Torch Fragment
14867.description: Broken piece left after the destruction of the Brazier of Purity built around the Ritual Site of Purge. Gather all and bring them to Dr. Helvetica in the Field of Silence Development Research Center.

14868.name: Guardian Spirit Fragment
14868.description: Broken piece of Guardian Spirit acquired from destroying the Magic Force Guardian Spirit and Evil Spirit in the Magic Force near the Ritual Site of Purge. Gather all and bring them to Dr. Helvetica in the Field of Silence Development Research Center.

14869.name: Destroyed machine piece
14869.description: This is a part you salvaged from one of the Landfill Machines you destroyed. Once you have collected 10 pieces, return to Athenia.

14870.name: Enchanted Golem Shard
14870.description: Fragment obtained from the destruction of the Suppressors and Exterminators belonging to Dr. Helvetica. Collect 20 fragments, then return to Athenia in the Field of Whispers.

14871.name: Mucrokian Hide
14871.description: This hide was obtained by killing a Mucrokian. When you are ready, return to Katensa to trade your hides for a reward.

14872.name: Awakened Mucrokian Hide
14872.description: Proof of defeating an Awakened Mucrokian. Gather and bring them to Katensa of the Field of Silence Research Center.

14873.name: Mucrokian Hide
14873.description: This hide was obtained by killing a Mucrokian. When you are ready, return to Priestess Athenia to trade your hides for a reward.

14874.name: Fallen Mucrokian Hide
14874.description: This hide was obtained by defeating a Contaminated Mucrokian. When you are ready, return to Priestess Athenia to trade these hides for a reward.

14875.name: Mineral Fragment
14875.description: Mineral fragment obtained as proof of defeating the enemies in the Mithril Mines. Collect and bring them to representative Filaur of the Grey Column guild at the Dwarven Village Chief Hall.

14876.name: Evidence of Migration
14876.description: Proof received from the Red Man Robbers that you have succeeded in convincing them. Collect and bring them to Grave Robber Leader Kanemika.

14877.name: Replenished Power Bead
14877.description: Bead needed to replenish the energy of power in Lucien's altar. Take it to each of Lucien's altars and enhance the energy of power.

14878.name: Discharged Power Bead
14878.description: Discharged power bead that has replenished Lucien's altar as a replenished power bead. Also proof that replenishment is complete. When all replenishments are complete, take this bead as proof of the mission's completion to the Priest of the Earth Daichir in Maphr's Temple in the Dwarven Village.

14879.name: Stakato Fang
14879.description: Fangs obtained from Stakato carcasses. Once you have 25, take them to Bounty Hunter Kintaijin.

14880.name: Dirty Bead
14880.description: Part of an artifact stolen by Billy Haari, these beads are obtained by defeating monsters inside the Stakato's Nest. Once you have 500, return to Kintaijin to receive your reward.

14881.name: Soul Core Containing Evil Spirit
14881.description: Monster's soul core containing an evil spirit. Small jewel with evil energy appearing in dark purple.

14882.name: Ragna Orc's Amulet
14882.description: Doll used in shamanism to control the evil creatures by the Ragna Orcs. Collect and bring them to Beacon Town Manager Torrant at the Den of Evil.

14883.name: Hisilrome's Heart
14883.description: Heart obtained after defeating Shilen's Priest Hisilrome.
